    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Door Trim Panel</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1603812" svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Door Trim Panel</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Removal procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Trim panel procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1603858" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1603858.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Trim Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. INNER DOOR PULL CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MAP POCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. COURTESY LIGHT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. TRIM PANEL FASTENER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. CAB DOOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two screws and inner door pull cup.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two screws from map pocket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully pull map pocket away from trim panel and disconnect electrical connector from
                    courtesy light, if applicable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove map pocket.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If equipped with manual windows and door locks, follow the next step. If equipped with power
                        windows and door locks, skip this step.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press in on trim panel near window handle shaft, insert proper removal tool, and remove
                    retaining clip and handle (not shown).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the interior trim tool, remove nine trim panel fasteners.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603859" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1603859.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Trim Panel Electrical Connectors</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL CONNECTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. ELECTRIC WINDOW AND DOOR LOCK SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift trim panel away from cab door and disconnect electrical connectors, if
                    applicable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove trim panel and place on a suitable, padded surface.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Installation procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Trim panel procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connectors to trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603859">Figure 78, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>), if applicable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Ensure electrical connector for courtesy light is pulled through before securing trim panel.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position trim panel in place on door and press firmly on each of the nine fasteners to
                    secure trim panel to cab door (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603858">Figure 77, Items 3, 7, and 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to courtesy light, if applicable (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603858">Figure 77, Item 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install map pocket with two screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603858">Figure 77, Items 3 and 5</hotlnk>). Tighten screws to 20 to 25 Lbf-in. (2
                    to 3 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door pull cup with two screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603858">Figure 77, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Tighten screws to 20 to 25 Lbf-in. (2
                    to 3 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If equipped with manual windows and door locks, follow the next step. If equipped with power
                        windows and door locks, skip this step.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install retaining clip and window handle. Press firmly onto window handle until it locks
                    into place (not shown).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
